<h1> About page</h1>
<p>Crypto Coins is a Ruby on Rails web application that provides users with information about cryptocurrencies using data retrieved from the Coinranking API.</p>
<p>
The application stores cryptocurrency data in a relational database consisting of two primary tables: Coins and Coin Details. The Coins table contains general information about each cryptocurrency, including its unique identifier (UUID), name, symbol, market rank, current price, market capitalization, 24-hour trading volume, price change percentage, tier, and icon URL. This information is used to provide users with a searchable list of cryptocurrencies.
</p>
<p>
The Coin Details table stores additional information for each cryptocurrency, including its description, official website, number of markets, number of exchanges, and price change data. Each coin detail record is linked to a corresponding coin using the cryptocurrency UUID, creating a one-to-one relationship between the two tables.</p>
<p>
Data is imported from the Coinranking API and stored locally in the database to improve application performance and reduce the number of external API requests required when users search for cryptocurrency information. Users can search for cryptocurrencies by name or symbol and view detailed information on a dedicated details page.</p>

<p>
The purpose of this application is to demonstrate database design, API integration, data relationships, and search functionality within a Ruby on Rails environment while providing useful cryptocurrency market information.
</p>
